Newell Smith Wallbank (26 April 1875 - 23 June 1945) was a British composer of pipe organ music.
He was Organist of Wakefield Cathedral from 1930 until his death in 1945.

response: *Newell Smith Wallbank 1911–1917 (later organist of Wakefield Cathedral)
*Newell Smith Wallbank 1918–1926 (later organist of Wakefield Cathedral)

The cathedral has had six organists since 1888, of which Jonathan Bielby, MBE was the longest serving organist in an English cathedral. Previous organists have included composer Newell Smith Wallbank. Assistant organists have included William Frederick Dunnill and John Scott.
